Of 85 patients, 45 (50.6%) completed all 5 evaluable PK profiles. Steady-state tacrolimus area under the curve, 0 to 24 hours (AUC0–24) and minimum concentration (Cmin) were comparable for both formulations, with treatment ratio means of 90.5% (90% confidence intervals [CI], 86.4%–94.6%) and 87.4% (95% CI, 82.9%–92.0%), respectively (acceptance interval, 80%–125%). There was good correlation between AUC0–24 and Cmin for tacrolimus QD (r = 0.94) and BID (r = 0.91). The relationship between these 2 parameters was also similar.
